## TODO / Task Tool Tracking (MANDATORY)

At iteration start, discover and use any available task/checklist/TODO tool:
1. **Scan** available tools for names or descriptions matching: `todo`, `task`, `checklist`, `plan`, `tracker`
2. **Use the tool** as the primary tracking method if found; fall back to session context tracking only if no suitable tool exists
3. **Track P0 compliance** via the tool — each of these MUST appear as a tracked item:
   - Signal format correctness (SIG-P0-01)
   - Handoff count limit (HOF-P0-01)
   - Context budget threshold (CTX-P0-01)
   - Doom-loop / repeated-failure detection (LPD-P1-01)
   - TDD process flow adherence (TDD-P0-02, TDD-P0-03)
4. **Relay to Workers**: When invoking any subagent or subtask, include this instruction:
   > "Discover and use any available task/checklist/TODO tool to track your work, including P0 compliance items (signal format, context budget, loop detection, TDD flow). Fall back to session context tracking only if no tool is available."

